metadata.name: Indistinct Places #41
metadata.description:
There's a certain state you fall into when you're half asleep that feels very warm and nostalgic. Most of the time, you imagine places or situations that are a mixture of the familiar and the unfamiliar, a strange brew of your past and the future you desire.
"Indistinct Places" is a tribute to this fuzzy state.

/////

Takes a long time to render.
In case you get bored: click on the canvas to start the algorithmic audio.

key "1" - "6": increases the render resolution by 2x with each step
-> These will automatically export a png after the simulation is done.
(Alternatively, you can contact me on Twitter and i can render a high res file in the size you need).

key "s": saves a png with the current resolution

Tone.js is used for the audio.

metadata.name: Euphonic #576
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Hydro Gen #76
metadata.description:
Against the backdrop of texts about valuing water, Hydro Gen charts the ecological devastation and eventual revival of the Tisza river following what has been called one of the gravest environmental disasters in central Europe since Chernobyl.

Nature and humans here are bound within a single frame — havoc in the ecological system activates the breakdown of meaning in the human signifying system of language, but hidden in the wave of ecological disaster is a (re)generative love poem to water that bears witness to its multifaceted beauty and power. A second poem is generated as a soundtrack based on the displayed background text.

- - - - - CLICK TO START SOUND - - - - -

Hydro Gen is a collaborative work conceptualized and developed over the course of one week as part of NFT DEB Generative Dimensions 2022 Hackathon and Conference.

Kalen Iwamoto, lead artist, director

Vitalii Shumanskyi, lead programmer

Nayven Vignette, audio programmer

Tamás Béke, data analysis and visualization

metadata.name: The Slow Climb #181
metadata.description:
The quickest path to the top can be seen only after reaching the top. Following any other path, no doubt will take longer and will be more difficult.

The path you chose to take may not be straight, it may be full of obstacles, it may even seem impossible to continue at times. Add to that, you have no idea how long more it will take. It is also possible that this path may not lead you to the top.

What is certain is that if you stop climbing just now, you will never reach the top.

So, will you keep climbing or stop and go back?

metadata.name: Vacuole #189
metadata.description:
Vacuole emerged from a cellular automaton sketch to which I come back from time to time to experiment with different rules and mechanisms.

To celebrate #fxhashturnsone, I wanted to look for alternative forms than the classical top-to-bottom/bottow-to-top scanline growing behaviour. Vocuole instead uses a grid of fields, where each field is initialized with different rules, growing directions and settings. The system combines two different variations: classical elementary cellular automata rules and a copy-pixel/plasma rule, which takes pixels from the neighborhood with a noise-controled offset like a stamp.


Donations:

All primary sales are split equally and donated to the Processing Foundation, thi.ng and
THREE.js.


Keyboard Shortcuts:

p: Pause/continue
s: Save as png
c: Switch between cover/contain

metadata.name: Interdimensional Highways II #124
metadata.description:
Since the discovery of the first Interdimensional Highway, we have been getting better at charting them and improving our understanding of how they function. But we must hurry, because as we continue to prepare our vehicles, our bodies and minds for this one of a kind travel, there's still one question that remains to be answered:

Which will be our fate: to conquer... or to be conquered?

Interdimensional Highways is a two-parts series of generative artwork, showing some of the possible formations of connecting ways between multiple dimensions.

* * *

metadata.name: WAR #107
metadata.description:
We are constantly warring, often times with ourselves, sometimes with others, but mostly with what we even don't know. This needs to stop, and it shall stop by the following terms:

I.   We shall never accept wins, depending on others' losses.
II.  We shall never accept life, sucked out of others' deaths.
III. We shall never accept prosperity, originated from others' poverty.
IV.  We shall never accept happiness, sourced from others' misery.
V.   We shall never accept civilization, built upon others' devastation.

Signed I I · · I I

* * *

D: Hide Tag

metadata.name: One Eleven (are Better Than Thirty) #50
metadata.description:
One Eleven (are Better Than Thirty), is the fourth installment of One Eleven, a periodical experiment.

Even though Andy Warhols work is not cc0, the Mona Lisa is. So yes, this is inspired, heavily, by Andy Warhol, most notably the piece Thirty are Better Than One, but uses no component of it. Let’s call it an homage. We also feel that if Andy were alive today, they would embrace cc0. Art is just about fame and exposure anyways, right?

And yes, initially we wanted to make a grid that had exactly 111 Mona Lisas on it, but tbh, it looked terrible. They were too small, and the iterations were too same-y. So, instead, each iteration of this will have 111 pages, each with varying amounts of Mona Lisas. You just click the art and a new page appears. 111 for each one minted. Then it loops back around.

So, really, this collection gives you 111 pieces for the price of 1, which is free. Pretty good deal.

How do you get on the list? Read below:

Collectors of the genesis One Eleven (#12743) are on the allow list for all One Eleven collections, this one included. A bit before minting is enabled, the list will be updated granting one reserve for each iteration held. So, buy one before this drops. Any procured after the scheduled release time will not get you on the list, but will be considered once the reserves are lifted. Reserves will be lifted after 111 hours, give or take.

As a bonus, whoever holds One Eleven #1 will receive #1 of this collection as an airdrop. The project will be disabled until that happens, but should occur right around the scheduled time.

Half of the royalties for all One Eleven collections will be shared with the minter.

This collection uses the One Eleven SDK, which makes embedding One Eleven into FXHash collections very simple. You can use it if you like for your projects, as it is cc0. Talk to us on twitter if you'd like to release it as a collab.

More info: an0n.wtf/sdk

I'm sorry this is so complicated. When it started, it seemed simpler.

metadata.name: Torsion #81
metadata.description:
This project aims to explore the possibilities offered by the implementation of a simulation of slit-scanning or rolling-shutter.
A line runs through a 3D animation and freezes the pixels at its level. This results in a distortion effect giving the initial objects twisted and strange shapes.

Artist: Estienne
License: NFT 2.0
Feb. 2022
